# File: bigcam/usr/share/biglinux/bigcam/ui/about_dialog.py, line: 39
msgid ""
"The universal webcam control center for Linux.\n"
"\n"
"BigCam was born as a small shell script so that Rafael Ruscher could use his Canon Rebel T3 as a "
"webcam during live streams about BigLinux. That humble hack, written by Rafael and Barnabé di "
"Kartola, evolved from a Bash bridge between gPhoto2 and FFmpeg into a full GTK4/Adwaita application "
"with live preview, multi-backend camera support (V4L2, gPhoto2, libcamera, PipeWire, IP cameras, "
"smartphones), real-time OpenCV effects, virtual camera output, photo and video capture, and 29 "
"languages."
msgstr ""
"Det universelle webcam kontrolcenter til Linux.\n"
"\n"
"BigCam blev født som et lille shell-script, så Rafael Ruscher kunne bruge sin Canon Rebel T3 som et "
"webcam under livestreams om BigLinux. Den ydmyge hack, skrevet af Rafael og Barnabé di Kartola, "
"udviklede sig fra en Bash-bro mellem gPhoto2 og FFmpeg til en fuld GTK4/Adwaita-applikation med "
"live forhåndsvisning, multi-backend kamerastøtte (V4L2, gPhoto2, libcamera, PipeWire, IP-kameraer, "
"smartphones), realtids OpenCV-effekter, virtuel kamerautgang, foto- og videooptagelse og 29 sprog."
